This info is about the Mad Max 35th Anniversary DVD with the red cover. It does indeed have the original Australian audio in case you were wondering. It also has the US audio track too. It also has a choice of Widescreen 2.35:1 or Full Screen 1.33:1. It also has a few special features like short documentaries, trailers and commentary. This is a DVD version mind you not a Blue Ray.

I have spent nearly 35 years watching Mad Max on an ancient VHS tape whenever the urge for Mad Max hit me.  This Version has additional footage I'd never seen before, and was glad to view.  The sound clarity and sharper DVD picture was of coarse most welcome!!

Saw this as a kid and thought it was the coolest thing I had ever seen. I purchased it to show to my car guy roommate who kept hearing it referenced in his car shows. No longer a kid, I thought it wasn't as good but was still cool and fun to watch. My roommate hated it and walked out of the room announcing that if he had gone to see it in a theater he would demand his money back. His loss.
